value.0: This seagull is huge! Its growth appears to have been accelerated by positive energy - and it's not happy!
A rather imposing grey crustacean with menacing, giant pincers that snap at all things non-crab indiscriminately. Its growth appears to have been accelerated by positive energy - and it's not happy!
A giant tailless amphibian with a short squat body, moist smooth skin, and very long hind legs for leaping. Its growth appears to have been accelerated by positive energy - and it's not happy!
This Turtle is huge! Its growth appears to have been accelerated by positive energy - and it's not happy!
This alligator is enormous! Its growth appears to have been accelerated by positive energy - and it's not happy!
Corpses reanimated through necromancy, zombies are mindless undead that shamble about, trying to satiate the dull ache of hunger in their decaying gut.
The bones of the dead, animated by dark magic, skeletons have no mind of their own.
Wraiths are incorporeal creatures born of evil and darkness. They despise all living things, as well as the light that nurtures them.
The bones of the dead, animated by dark magic, skeletons have no mind of their own.

The wizard Arcimus was heralded as a creative genius by some and as a lunatic by others. However, everybody agreed that Arcimus knew how to wreak havoc and devastation. 

His whereabouts and status are unknown after a strange accident that destroyed his tower, but since that time items bearing his name have appeared around the Isles. 

(Page Class)
The Great Arcimus' Lesser Boom Stick
These undead carrion eaters haunt the graveyards and battlefields that bore them, still bearing the rotting flesh they once wore in life.
These bats are vicious little bloodsuckers, with fangs sharper than the rest of their kin.
Wights are undead creatures, the remains of those that delved too far and too long into the black arts.
With red eyes and a feral visage, this creature is surely a vampire.
